init_text: A woman has been dating guy after guy, but it never seems to work out. She's unaware that she's actually been dating the same guy over and over; a shapeshifter who's fallen for her, and is certain he's going to get it right this time.

actions.name: text-insert
actions.text: But he's able to convince her each time that it's the real him, and not a copy.

actions.name: text-insert
actions.text: He has her thinking he's a real superhero now, with superpowers.

actions.name: text-insert
actions.text: Can she ever see through his charade?

actions.name: text-insert
actions.text: And why won't he tell her who he really is?

actions.name: text-insert
actions.text: She confronts him, and he reveals the truth.

actions.name: text-insert
actions.text: He's able to convince her it's the truth by showing her his true form.

actions.name: text-insert
actions.text: The woman can't believe her eyes.

actions.name: text-insert
actions.text: He shows her all his other forms as proof it was him.

actions.name: text-insert
actions.text: He was just telling me what I wanted to hear, she realized.
